@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    The AskConf door is used to check that the uploads files are
    for the current conference.

    This door can be removed if you don't want it's functionality,
    just remove it from any "Commnds/System" file that is used in.

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The doors is stored as HBBS:Doors/System/AskConf/AskConf.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.0.  V1.04 introduced a @{"config file" link ConfigFiles} which you
    should edit.

    There are two entries for this door in the commands/system file:

    AskConf_Type_1=HBBS
    AskConf_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/AskConf/AskConf.HBBS {N} {O}

    PreCheck_Type_1=HBBS
    PreCheck_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/AskConf/AskConf.HBBS {N} {O}
    PreCheck_Param_1=REMOVEFLAG

    See HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/System.

@EndNode

@Node SystemOptions "SystemOptions"

  System Options
  ==============

    REMOVEFLAG - If specified the door will remove it's flag file.
                 this option is used before CheckFiles starts, via
                 the PreCheck system door name.

@EndNode

@Node CmdLineOptions "CmdLineOptions"

  Command Line Options
  ====================

    <filename> - Filename of uploaded file to be checked, Must be specified
    if REMOVEFLAG system option is not specified.

@EndNode

@Node ScreensDisplayed "Screens Displayed"

  Screens Displayed
  =================

    None

@EndNode

@Node DoorsCalled "Doors Called"

  Doors Called
  ============

    None

@EndNode

@Node Returns "Returns"

  Returned Values (in N_ND->DoorReturn)
  =====================================

    "0" if no conference was picked for some reason.
    <confnum> if a conference was picked.


@EndNode

@Node ConfigFiles "ConfigFiles"

  Config Files
  ============

    This door now has an optional config file since V1.04.

    It is opened using "Progdir:AskConf.CFG", e.g.

    HBBS:Doors/System/AskConf/AskConf.CFG

    You cannot use comments in this file, and trailing spaces
    will NOT be stripped from config items.

    ANSI escape sequences *CAN* be used.

  Options
  =======

    AllForThisConf=<String>    @{" More... " link CFG_AllForThisConf}
    ForThisConf=<String>       @{" More... " link CFG_ForThisConf}
    RemainingFiles=<String>    @{" More... " link CFG_RemainingFiles}
    UsingConf=<String>         @{" More... " link CFG_UsingConf}

@EndNode

@Node CFG_AllForThisConf "AllForThisConf"

  AllForThisConf=<string>

    E.G.

    AllForThisConf=Are all files for the @C@ conference ?

    Default is internal any may be changed.

    When the door is called with the REMOVEFLAG option, the user
    will be asked this question.

    If the string contains @C@, it will be replaced with the conference name

@EndNode

@Node CFG_ForThisConf "ForThisConf"

  ForThisConf=<String>

    E.G.

    ForThisConf=Use the @C@ conference for @F@ ?

    Default is internal and may be changed.

    When the door is called with a filename as the option (e.g. by CheckFiles
    just after the file ID has been displayed) the user is asked this question

    If they answer NO, then they will be shown a list of conferences to use
    instead of the one they're in.

    They will then be asked if the wish to use the selected conference for the
    rest of the uploaded files.  See @{"RemainingFiles" link CFG_RemainingFiles}

    If the string contains @C@, it will be replaced with the conference name
    If the string contains @F@, it will be replaced by the filename

@EndNode

@Node CFG_RemainingFiles "RemainingFiles"

  RemainingFiles=<string>

    E.G.

    RemainingFiles=Use the @C@ conference for remaining files ?

    Default is internal and may be changed.

    This is shown if the user picked a different conference for the file,
    and there are more files to be checked after the current one.

    If the string contains @C@, it will be replaced with the conference name

@EndNode

@Node CFG_UsingConf "UsingConf"

  UsingConf=<string>

    E.G.

    UsingConf=Using the @C@ conference for @F@

    Default is internal and may be changed.

    This message is displayed when the user has selected a conference to use
    for all the files or the remaining files.

    If the string contains @C@, it will be replaced with the conference name
    If the string contains @F@, it will be replaced by the filename

@EndNode

@Node ToDo "ToDo"

  ToDo
  ====

    Optimise, so that the AskConflist.TXT's are not loaded several times
    when checking more than one tag at a time. (Arghh..)

    Option for free download dates and times (i.e. if the user calls between
    two times or between two times on a specified date or on a specified date
    then make *all* the downloads free! add another flag called
    TF_FREEDOWNLOADTHISCALL so that the TF_FREEDOWNLOAD flag could be removed
    at loggoff.

    This requires working around the fact that a user could call, flag files
    and log off with them still flagged.  so the best way of getting round
    this would be to call the AskConf door, when the user logs off, with
    another option so that it can remove the TF_FREEDOWNLOAD flag if the
    TF_FREEDOWNLOADTHISCALL is set.

    Then at login time, all flagged files with TF_FREEDOWNLOADTHISCALL
    have to be rechecked, simply by calling this door with no paramaters.

@EndNode

